frameDefinitions: An Agent saves a Patient or an Asset from a Harmful_situation.
The action of an Agent or the occurrence of a Cause event returns an Entity to an earlier  state of vigor and strength.
This frame concerns rituals performed in line with religious beliefs or tradition.
This frame includes words that name medical specialties and is closely related to the Medical_professionals frame.
An Agent finishes an Activity, which can no longer logically continue.
frameExamples: Israeli commandos <t>rescued</t> the hostages and left.
Falling prices and wireless connectivity have <t>breathed new life</t> into the PDA market.
In certain fertility <t>rites</t> in Burma , a woman desirous of offspring is required not only to approach the King Cobra but to plant a kiss on its mouth .
Jason <t>completed</t> grading the papers late Sunday night.
listRoleDefinitions: The sentient being who rescues the <fen>Patient</fen> or <fen>Asset</fen> from the <fen>Harmful_situation</fen>.
The living being who is rescued by the <fen>Agent</fen>.
The entity that is judged to be valueable which might be lost or damaged by the <fen>Harmful_situation</fen>.
An event that occurs which could result in injury or harm to the <fen>Patient</fen> or <fen>Asset</fen>.
The time at which the <fen>Agent</fen> rescues the <fen>Patient</fen> or <fen>Asset</fen>.
The location at which the <fen>Agent</fen> rescues the <fen>Patient</fen> or <fen>Asset</fen>.
The concrete or abstract thing that is brought into an earlier state in which it was more effective and powerful.
The <fen>Agent</fen> puts the <fen>Entity</fen> into a state of renewed vigor.
An event or state whose occurrence brings about the <fen>Entity</fen>'s return to a vigorous state.
This role identifies the time when the <fen>Agent</fen> causes the renewal of the <fen>Entity</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the Agent brings about the change in the <fen>Entity</fen>'s state.
This is the religious or cultural leader who performs and/or leads the rite.
The role <fen>Member</fen> describes the member of the religious or cultural group who participates in/undergoes the rite.
<fen>Organization</fen> identifies the institution in which the rite is prescribed.
This role identifies the <fen>Instrument</fen> used to perform a particular rite.
This role identifies the state which the rite is hoped or intended to bring about.
The type of ritual or ceremony being performed.
This role indicates an object on which a rite is performed.
Rites may confer a <fen>New_status</fen> on a participant (e.g. rank, membership).
The <fen>Guardian</fen> is the member of the <fen>Organization</fen> who instigates the rite for someone of which they are a guardian.
When the rite is performed
Where the rite takes place.
This role identifies the medical <fen>Specialty</fen> that someone practices.
This role identifies the <fen>Agent</fen> who has finished an <fen>Activity</fen>.
This role identifies the <fen>Activity</fen> that the <fen>Agent</fen> has finished.
This role identifies the <fen>Time</fen> when the <fen>Activity</fen> finishes.
This role identifies the <fen>Place</fen> where the <fen>Agent</fen> finishes the <fen>Activity</fen>.
